March 2021: 20 packages for each household - and a jump in weight
46.6 million parcels arrived in Israel during 2021 - similar to 2020
The average weight per package stands at 435 grams - a 36% jump from 2020
The busiest month: December, when the average package weighed 524 grams.
In 2021, 46.6 million packages arrived in Israel, almost 20 packages on average per household - according to Israel Post data obtained by Israel Today.
The number of packages that arrived in 2021 is similar to 2020, when 46.5 million packages arrived in Israel, and lower than 2019 - when 61.6 million packages arrived.
Even so, this year there has been an annual increase of more than 36 percent in the weight of packages from abroad.
In 2021, 20,253 tons of products arrived in Israel from abroad, a jump of 36 percent from 14,860 tons in 2020, and 16,743 tons in 2019.
Changes in consumption habits
The average weight of a package has climbed by 60 percent in two years - from 272 grams in 2019 to 435 grams in 2021.
The increase in the pack weight is mainly influenced by two major trends, both on the seller and the buyer side: Large overseas shopping sites are uniting items for single delivery, and are no longer sending each product from the shopping cart in separate packaging.
On the Israeli consumer side, the fast delivery of the shipments, within a few days of ordering, supports the purchase of more everyday goods such as clothing and gifts, which the buyers wish to receive nearby when the purchase is made.
In 2021, as in 2020 and 2019, the month with the highest weight and number of packages arriving from overseas was also December, with 4.2 million packages weighing a total of 2,200 tons.
In December the average weight of each package was 13 ounces [524 g], 20 percent above the annual average.
Black Friday effect
More packages arrived in December than any other month, likely due to the November shopping holidays, such as Chinese Singles' Day, Black Friday and Cyber Monday.
The big orders start arriving in Israel a week or two after the purchase.
