Dr. Schinfeldt taught me to listen very carefully to many things: to listen to the children, to listen to the monitor, to listen to the nurses, to the care teams both young and old, and listen to the parents.
And all of this needs to be done not only to communicate more correctly and more efficiently, but to continually gather the information that can prevent the next downturn.
